author: glyn
msg: Create interop. round 3, group E cross-checking client.
The client has an input parameter of a URI of a WSDL file provided
for the service we are testing against. The client introspects the
WSDL to determine the service and port names that the implementer has
chosen. The client then invokes the echoLinkedList operation after
registering suitable serializer and deserializer factories for the
list type (which is not allowed to vary by implementer according
to the rules for group E).
See http://www.whitemesa.net/r3/interop3.html for a test plan and
live endpoints.
